Hey all - I am trying to write a script to limit the number of records that can pass through a custom coded module to the next step to 120. 

I would then like to send any additional records to a static list.

I am yet to a test this - but would like some thoughts on it, before I do - just in case I missed something. 


// define a variable to keep track of the number of records that have passed through the module

var recordCount = 0;

// define the HubSpot static list ID

var listId = '123456';

// define a function that checks whether the maximum number of records has been reached

function canPassThrough() {
  return recordCount &lt; 120;
}

// use the function to control the flow of records through the module

if (canPassThrough()) {

 // do something with the record

 recordCount++;
} else {

 // add the record to the static list
  var contactId = {{contact.id}};
  var apiUrl = '<https://api.hubapi.com/contacts/v1/lists/|https://api.hubapi.com/contacts/v1/lists/>' + listId + '/add?contactId=' + contactId;
  fetch(apiUrl, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    },
  })
  .then(response =&gt; response.json())
  .then(data =&gt; console.log(data))
  .catch(error =&gt; console.error(error));
}

Hey all!

I'm trying to use the `/crm/v3/associations/{fromObjectType}/{toObjectType}/batch/read` API endpoint to get a list of associated companies for a set of deals, but unfortunately it seems inconsistent with the v4, or maybe I'm making the wrong request.

This is an example using just one deal ID:
`POST /crm/v3/associations/Deals/Companies/batch/read`
Body:
```{
  "inputs": [
    { "id": "TEST_DEAL_ID_1" }
  ]
}```
And I have in response:
```...
"status": "error",
"category": "OBJECT_NOT_FOUND",
"subCategory": "crm.associations.NO_ASSOCIATIONS_FOUND",
"message": "No company is associated with deal TEST_DEAL_ID_1.",
...```
Which is not correct, as there are companies associated with the deal.

In fact, if I try to use the v4 association API, it works fine (but I can't do batch, so it forces me to do a lot of API calls):
`GET /crm/v4/objects/deal/TEST_DEAL_ID_1/associations/company`
Response:
```{
  "results": [
    {
      "toObjectId": TEST_COMPANY_ID_1,
      "associationTypes": [...]
    },
    {
      "toObjectId": TEST_COMPANY_ID_2,
      "associationTypes": [...]
    }
  ]
}```
Interestingly, the v3 api seems to works fine for Companies-Contacts associations, e.g.
`POST /crm/v3/associations/Companies/Contacts/batch/read`
Body:
```{
  "inputs": [
    { "id": "TEST_COMPANY_ID_1" },
    { "id": "TEST_COMPANY_ID_2" }
  ]
}```
Response:
```...
"results": [
  {
    "from": {"id": "TEST_COMPANY_ID_1"},
    "to": [... full list of associated contacts ...]
  },
  {
    "from": {"id": "TEST_COMPANY_ID_2"},
    "to": [... full list of associated contacts ...]
  }
...```
Has this issue happened to anybody else?

